<br>
Aside from the massive amount of bugs, (ESPECIALLY the memory leak which forces me to reboot every 30 mins) the gameplay concept in general is ingenious compared to EQ.  In comparison, everyone being able to walk into karnors with your group and have the zone to yourself and being able to actually dungeon crawl and hunt through the zone from room to room to the end boss is nice, even determining the level of the zone perportionally to your group size (easy to hard).  The same fun with fewer people works for me.  This game caters to the casual player enabling me to not spend 30 hrs organizing a raid that goes disasterously wrong because too many people that can't listen.  It rids the boredom of pulling mob spawns to a &quot;camp&quot; over and over.  It gets rid of the hours of corpse retrieval and waiting on GM support for corpse bugs.  All of that to me adds realism and fun rather than stress and boredom.  I know some people like to hunt the outdoor zones and I like that the option for that is there as well rather than doing missions.  I love doing missions with my RL friend, she and I can do it just us two with it set on 80% difficulty.   I'm just bored at work and blabbering though. Sorry to get on a tangent.  My point being regardless of the bugs and lack of support and security, just trying point out all the good concepts.  I see people bitching so much but if AO has managed to pull me from EQ as much as I'm not into the sci fi game thing, then there is definately something about it that is good.  Although the only time I play is when my friend is playing. <p><center><a href="http://www.silentsentinels.com"><img src="http://www.vanitey.com/signature.jpg" border=0 align=bottom></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"