People complain about the economy, the community, bugs, exploits, lack of support and the list goes on.  But like you said when you rush a product out, you'll have these problems.  I also think to an extent they *had* to release the game to the public eventually to find these problems.  In a small controlled environment, some problems won't show themselves..<br>
<br>
I have to admit, lately I've been really angry with the game only because of the memory issue.  I too need to reboot every 30 minutes or so.  Or several times just to get through a city.  That gets really old.  Last night while taking the whompa from Athens to Newland, I made a left hand turn to bolt to the exit.  I went ld due to the memory problem.  When I tried to get connected again I couldn't for over an hour.  I would log in.  Start seeing the graphics load and then it would pop me out to the desktop. I called it a night since I couldn't get in. This morning figuring that if it was due to the load and a lot of people being in there, that it would maybe work.  Needless to say I was able to move my char out of the zone.<br>
<br>
But all in all.  This game suits me a lot better then EQ.  Even though I spent a long time playing EQ...<br>
